To do a coredump in QNX:
  dumper -d /tmp -p proc_id &
This will include the trace log as well as variables.

proc_id is the process ID found in pidin
-d specifies the destination directory
The core dump is named as "process_name".core

Then you can copy the file to workstation and use qnx_gdb to look into it.

qnx_gdb binary_file core_file


By default, the dumper will dump the trace log but not the variables when
a process crash in /flash.  If you want to dump also the variables, you need to:
  first stop MPEG process from autostart
  mount NFS:
    ifconfig en2 1.14.80.42/24
    fs-nfs3 1.14.80.1:/tmp /mnt &
  slay dumper		// kill the default dumper
  dumper -d /tmp &	// start dumper again
  mpeg_process &	// then start mpeg_process
